ðŸ”¹ Step 3: Define Database Models (models.py)

Using SQLAlchemy for storing user preferences.

python
from flask_sqlalchemy import SQLAlchemy

db = SQLAlchemy()

class UserPreference(db.Model):
    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)
    user_id = db.Column(db.String(50), unique=True, nullable=False)
    meditation_type = db.Column(db.String(50), nullable=False)
    tone = db.Column(db.String(50), nullable=False)
    background_sound = db.Column(db.String(50), nullable=False)
    voice_type = db.Column(db.String(50), nullable=False)

ðŸ”¹ Step 4: Implement deepseek_service.py (Text + TTS API)

Handles DeepSeek API requests.

python
import requests
from config import Config

DEEPSEEK_TEXT_API = "https://api.deepseek.com/generate_text"
DEEPSEEK_TTS_API = "https://api.deepseek.com/convert_to_audio"

headers = {"Authorization": f"Bearer {Config.DEEPSEEK_API_KEY}"}

def generate_meditation_text(prompt):
    payload = {"prompt": prompt, "max_tokens": 300}
    response = requests.post(DEEPSEEK_TEXT_API, json=payload, headers=headers)
    return response.json().get("text", "")

def generate_tts(text):
    payload = {"text": text, "voice": "calm_male", "format": "mp3"}
    response = requests.post(DEEPSEEK_TTS_API, json=payload, headers=headers)
    return response.content  # Returns audio binary data

ðŸ”¹ Step 5: Implement Routes for Text & TTS (routes/text_gen.py & routes/tts.py)

Text Generation Route

python
from flask import Blueprint, request, jsonify
from services.deepseek_service import generate_meditation_text

text_gen_bp = Blueprint("text_gen", __name__)

@text_gen_bp.route("/generate_text", methods=["POST"])
def generate_text():
    data = request.json
    prompt = f"Generate a {data['length']} meditation in a {data['tone']} tone about {data['theme']}."
    text = generate_meditation_text(prompt)
    return jsonify({"meditation_text": text})

TTS Route

python
from flask import Blueprint, request, send_file
from services.deepseek_service import generate_tts
import io

tts_bp = Blueprint("tts", __name__)

@tts_bp.route("/generate_tts", methods=["POST"])
def generate_tts_audio():
    data = request.json
    text = data["text"]
    audio_data = generate_tts(text)
    return send_file(io.BytesIO(audio_data), mimetype="audio/mpeg", as_attachment=True, download_name="meditation.mp3")

ðŸ”¹ Step 6: Implement AI-Generated Background Sound (audio_service.py)

We use WaveGAN (GAN-based) for realistic ambient noise.

python
import torch
import librosa
import numpy as np
from pydub import AudioSegment
from my_gan_model import WaveGAN  # Load pretrained GAN model

def generate_background_noise(sound_type):
    model = WaveGAN.load_pretrained("wavegan_" + sound_type)
    noise = model.generate()
    return librosa.output.write_wav("background_noise.wav", noise, sr=16000)

Background Noise Route (routes/audio_gen.py)

python
from flask import Blueprint, request, send_file
from services.audio_service import generate_background_noise

audio_gen_bp = Blueprint("audio_gen", __name__)

@audio_gen_bp.route("/generate_audio", methods=["POST"])
def generate_audio():
    data = request.json
    sound_type = data["sound_type"]
    audio_path = generate_background_noise(sound_type)
    return send_file(audio_path, mimetype="audio/wav")

ðŸ”¹ Step 7: Implement User Preferences Handling (user_service.py)

Handles storing & retrieving user preferences.

python
from models import db, UserPreference

def save_user_preferences(user_id, meditation_type, tone, background_sound, voice_type):
    pref = UserPreference.query.filter_by(user_id=user_id).first()
    if pref:
        pref.meditation_type = meditation_type
        pref.tone = tone
        pref.background_sound = background_sound
        pref.voice_type = voice_type
    else:
        pref = UserPreference(
            user_id=user_id,
            meditation_type=meditation_type,
            tone=tone,
            background_sound=background_sound,
            voice_type=voice_type
        )
        db.session.add(pref)
    db.session.commit()

User Preferences Route (routes/user.py)

python
from flask import Blueprint, request, jsonify
from services.user_service import save_user_preferences

user_bp = Blueprint("user", __name__)

@user_bp.route("/save_preferences", methods=["POST"])
def save_preferences():
    data = request.json
    save_user_preferences(
        user_id=data["user_id"],
        meditation_type=data["meditation_type"],
        tone=data["tone"],
        background_sound=data["background_sound"],
        voice_type=data["voice_type"]
    )
    return jsonify({"message": "Preferences saved successfully!"})

ðŸ”¹ Step 8: Integrate All Routes in app.py

python
from flask import Flask
from flask_sqlalchemy import SQLAlchemy
from config import Config
from routes.text_gen import text_gen_bp
from routes.tts import tts_bp
from routes.audio_gen import audio_gen_bp
from routes.user import user_bp
from models import db

app = Flask(__name__)
app.config.from_object(Config)
db.init_app(app)

# Register Blueprints
app.register_blueprint(text_gen_bp, url_prefix="/api")
app.register_blueprint(tts_bp, url_prefix="/api")
app.register_blueprint(audio_gen_bp, url_prefix="/api")
app.register_blueprint(user_bp, url_prefix="/api")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)

5ï¸âƒ£ Define User Preferences Route (routes/user.py)

python
from flask import Blueprint, request, jsonify
from services.user_service import save_user_preferences
from models import db, UserPreference

user_bp = Blueprint("user", __name__)

@user_bp.route("/save_preferences", methods=["POST"])
def save_preferences():
    data = request.json
    save_user_preferences(
        user_id=data["user_id"],
        meditation_type=data["meditation_type"],
        tone=data["tone"],
        background_sound=data["background_sound"],
        voice_type=data["voice_type"]
    )
    return jsonify({"message": "Preferences saved successfully!"})

@user_bp.route("/get_preferences/<user_id>", methods=["GET"])
def get_preferences(user_id):
    pref = UserPreference.query.filter_by(user_id=user_id).first()
    if not pref:
        return jsonify({"error": "No preferences found"}), 404
    return jsonify({
        "user_id": pref.user_id,
        "meditation_type": pref.meditation_type,
        "tone": pref.tone,
        "background_sound": pref.background_sound,
        "voice_type": pref.voice_type
    })
